{North is to play 3NT. East leads the \H5, West plays the \H2.

Winners:   \S=2  \H=2  \D=1  \C=2  Total = 7

You are very lucky. Apparently East led from \H K Q so you won an undeserved \H trick. Now, if \Cs split 2-2 you can make 12 tricks! But hold it a minute. If you play dummy's two top \Cs and they <b>DON'T</b> split 2-2 you will only  win two \C tricks and the contract will fail. Instead you should play a small \C from dummy right now. The defenders will win the trick easily, but you will win their return and you will still have a \C to get to dummy's 6 \C winners!

Ducking a \C is the only way to make the contract and you might as well do it at the second trick.}
[Play "W"]H5

